Jose SerraSAO PAULO. Brazil s Foreign Minister Jose Serra resigned on Wednesday citing health concerns, in a new blow to Michel Temer s administration.Serra (74) said health problems made him unable to keep up with the rhythm of leading the foreign ministry of Latin America s biggest nation. He did not disclose what medical problems he is addressing. A government source said it was related to his spine on which he has had surgery in the past.Serra was a highly experienced official and former presidential candidate.Temer has low popularity ratings amid a vast corruption scandal. He took over as president in May to replace Dilma Rousseff, who was later impeached.Temer already had lost seven leading members of his government &#8211; six ministers and a senior adviser. AFP.